# ALIMIND — WATCHDOG SYSTEM FINAL DOCUMENT
VERSION: v2.2
STATUS: STABLE · LOCKED · PRODUCTION READY

## Role in System
DATA → HEALTH → WATCHDOG → HUMAN ALERT

## Core Features

### Central Logger
log_info / log_warn / log_error
INFO → off in SILENT_MODE
WARN / ERROR → always active

### Silent Mode
SILENT_MODE=true → removes noise, keeps only important logs

### Human-readable Alerts
❗ WATCHDOG
Модуль: <название>
Проблема: <простое объяснение>

⚠️ WATCHDOG
Модуль: <название>
Проблема: <простое объяснение>

### Issue Structure
{
  "id": "...",
  "level": "info | warning | critical",
  "kind": "...",
  "module": "...",
  "human_text": "..."
}

Kinds:
- system_error
- data_error
- stale_data
- expected_empty
- unexpected_empty
- internal_watchdog_error

### Noise Control
- Grouped stale alerts (multiple → one)
- Grouped module alerts
- Expected empty → no alert
- Critical → always individual

### Snapshot Structure
{
  "timestamp": "...",
  "status": "ok | warning | error",
  "health_score": 0-100,
  "modules": {...},
  "issues": [...],
  "alerts_sent": [...]
}

### Health Score
100
-30 critical
-10 warning
min = 0

### Anti-spam
should_alert()
save_alert()
+ grouped keys

